{"cursor":"15037","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n application|300px]]\n\n'Centrifugal pumps', are a sub-class of dynamic axisymmetric work-absorbing\nturbomachinery.  Centrifugal pumps are used to\ntransport liquids/fluids by the conversion of the rotational kinetic energy to\nthe hydro dynamics energy of the liquid flow. The rotational energy typically\ncomes from an engine or electric motor or turbine. In the typical simple case,\nthe fluid enters the pump impeller along or near to the rotating axis and is\naccelerated by the impeller, flowing radially outward into a diffuser or volute\nchamber (casing), from where it exits.\n\nCommon uses include water, sewage, petroleum and petrochemical pumping. The\nreverse function of the centrifugal pump is a water turbine converting potential\nenergy of water pressure into mechanical rotational energy.\n","linknr":246,"url":"Centrifugal_pump","recorded":1362482162,"links":52,"instances":["physics","pump","rotating_reference_frame"],"pdf":["http://turbolab.tamu.edu/proc/pumpproc/P21/01.pdf","http://turbolab.tamu.edu/proc/pumpproc/P21/01.pdf","http://authors.library.caltech.edu/25019/3/pumbook.pdf","http://authors.library.caltech.edu/28373/1/BRE252.pdf","http://authors.library.caltech.edu/28452/1/BRE241.pdf","http://authors.library.caltech.edu/28451/1/BRE240.pdf","http://authors.library.caltech.edu/2720/1/BRE225.pdf","http://authors.library.caltech.edu/25021/2/cabook.pdf","http://authors.library.caltech.edu/155/1/TSU200.pdf"],"categories":["Pumps","Compressors","Turbomachinery","Turbines","Thermodynamics","Fluid dynamics","Aerodynamics"],"headings":["History","How it works","Vertical centrifugal pumps","Froth pumps","Multistage centrifugal pumps","Energy usage","Problems of centrifugal pumps","Centrifugal pumps for solids control","Magnetically coupled pumps","Priming","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_bo